<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="429" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="35.[1399,2605,1553,2454]" pageId="35" pageNumber="429">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1401,1752,2188,2217]" pageId="35" pageNumber="429">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Endangered on The IUCN Red List (as C. mera). The Darien Small-eared Shrew has a very restricted distribution and is threatened mostly by deforestation and pesticides. It is found in the Darién National Park in Panama and can be common. Virtually nothing is known ofits natural history, and additional research is needed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
